Product Version     25.10    Cadence Design Systems, Inc.
read_parallel_edit_files(25.10)                read_parallel_edit_files(25.10)

Name
       read_parallel_edit_files  - Loads all the specified parallel edit files
       and implements the editing changes recorded in them

Syntax
       read_parallel_edit_files

       [-help]

       [-check]

       [-conflict_mode {only_one stop_all}]

       -files <list_of_files>

       [-ignore_error]

       [-report_file <file_name>]

       Loads all the specified parallel edit files and implements the  editing
       changes recorded in them.

       During  parallel  editing,  there is a possibility of a conflict if the
       same attribute of an object  is  changed  in  different  parallel  edit
       files. Some cases in which a conflict can occur are listed below:

              * Two users edit the layer of the same wire segment.

              * Two users edit the width of the same NDR rule.

              * One  user  cuts the wire segment, and another user changes the
                status of the same wire.

       In the following examples of parallel edits, there is no conflict:

              * One user edits the layer of wire, and another user  edits  its
                mask.

              * One  user edits the width of an NDR rule, and another user ed-
                its its spacing.

       In case of any conflict in the parallel edit files, the tool implements
       changes as per the specified conflict mode and writes  the  conflicting
       information to a report file.

       For  information  on  the parallel edit flow, format of a parallel edit
       file, and conflict handling examples see the "Parallel Editing Capabil-
       ity" section in the Editing Wires chapter of the Innovus User Guide.

Parameters
       -help  Prints a brief description that includes type and default infor-
              mation for each read_parallel_edit_files parameter.

              For a detailed description of the command and all of its parame-
              ters, use the man command:

              man read_parallel_edit_files

       -check Specifies that the tool should only check the  syntax  and  con-
              flict  of  the  files  but  should  not  actually  implement the
              changes.

       -conflict_mode {only_one stop_all}
              Specifies the conflict mode. The two possible modes are:

              * only_one - In case of conflicting  commands,  the  first  read
                command  is  implemented  and the other command is recorded in
                the conflict report.

              * stop_all - In case of conflicting commands,  the  tool  imple-
                ments  neither of the conflicting commands and records both of
                them in the conflict report.

       -files <list_of_files>
              Specifies the list of parallel editing files.

       -ignore_error
              Specifies whether errors in files should be ignored.  When  this
              option  is  specified,  the  tool skips lines with issues in the
              files but continues to read the other wires on the same net.

       -report_file <file_name>
              Specifies the name of the conflict report.

